00:13:38,430 --> 00:13:41,900
and just...inexcusable.

330
00:13:42,610 --> 00:13:44,780
But I'm guessing you're gonna give one anyway.

331
00:13:44,970 --> 00:13:45,720
No.

332
00:13:46,470 --> 00:13:50,350
No, just an explanation and a, uh...request.

333
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:53,700
It could help me to convince Andrews

334
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,340
I deserve a second chance.

335
00:13:56,030 --> 00:13:58,850
Okay. Let's hear the explanation.

336
00:13:59,820 --> 00:14:03,190
Dr. Browne and I are... seeing each other.

337
00:14:03,860 --> 00:14:05,820
Look, if you could just put yourself in my shoes.

338
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:08,480
A woman I care about tells me a guy harassed her,

339
00:14:08,870 --> 00:14:10,530
and, even worse, she tells me it's my fault

340
00:14:10,530 --> 00:14:13,540
because I was too -- too stupidly insensitive

341
00:14:13,540 --> 00:14:15,340
to understand what she was going through.

342
00:14:16,880 --> 00:14:18,090
I felt like crap.

343
00:14:18,420 --> 00:14:19,230
And like an idiot,

344
00:14:19,230 --> 00:14:22,770
I...tried to make it up to her.

345
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:29,230
All I'm asking for is just a little understanding.

346
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,400
Wouldn't you have done the same thing?

347
00:14:37,930 --> 00:14:39,380
Not my problem.

348
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:44,360
Yeah?

349
00:14:44,360 --> 00:14:46,170
Jenny's bradycardic and hypotensive.

350
00:14:46,170 --> 00:14:48,040
- What's happening? -She was fine a minute ago.

351
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:50,590
We were talking, then she started to have trouble breathing.

352
00:14:54,830 --> 00:14:56,170
Jenny's heart is failing.

353
00:14:57,590 --> 00:14:58,530
No pulse.

354
00:14:58,620 --> 00:15:00,920
She's in V-tach. Grab the cart, page Melendez.

355
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:10,630
Jenny's stable.

356
00:15:10,730 --> 00:15:13,210
I have her on beta blockers and vasodilators,

357
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:14,360
but it's not gonna be enough.

358
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:15,590
Renal-vein rupture must have caused

359
00:15:15,590 --> 00:15:17,680
her already weak heart to deteriorate.

360
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:18,790
She's in end-stage failure.

361
00:15:18,790 --> 00:15:20,070
I'll get her on the transplant registry.

362
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,840
What are we talking? Months? Weeks?

363
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:22,930
Days.

364
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:25,480
We're not gonna find a donor heart in a few days.

365
00:15:28,530 --> 00:15:31,850
We could disconnect her from the other body

366
00:15:31,850 --> 00:15:34,710
her heart is partially oxygenating the blood for.

367
00:15:36,180 --> 00:15:37,440
I was already pushing the envelope

368
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,620
to do the separation surgery

369
00:15:38,620 --> 00:15:40,830
six months after a kidney transplant.

370
00:15:40,830 --> 00:15:41,330
Do you really think

371
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:43,150
they could handle it one day after?

372
00:15:44,910 --> 00:15:46,440
It may be our only choice.

373
00:15:49,570 --> 00:15:50,300
Yeah.

375
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:56,770
His calls are an even bigger buzzkill than this rain

376
00:15:56,770 --> 00:15:58,810
and defeating the whole purpose of this trip.

377
00:15:59,220 --> 00:15:59,950
Okay.

378
00:16:01,210 --> 00:16:04,450
Residents are not supposed to turn off their phones.

379
00:16:06,040 --> 00:16:07,560
How about we make a deal?

380
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:11,310
If you turn off your phone, I'll let you drive.

381
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:14,200
- I don't have a driver's license. - I know.

382
00:16:14,900 --> 00:16:17,770
- I've always wanted to learn to drive. - I know.

383
00:16:17,770 --> 00:16:20,200
Dr. Glassman -- he never wanted me to.

384
00:16:20,200 --> 00:16:20,990
I know.

385
00:16:21,240 --> 00:16:22,210
Actually, I didn't know that,

386
00:16:22,210 --> 00:16:24,090
but that definitely sounds like Glassy.

387
00:16:27,230 --> 00:16:28,060
Okay.

388
00:16:28,170 --> 00:16:28,890
Yeah?

389
00:16:35,980 --> 00:16:37,650
You're doing awesome.

390
00:16:38,340 --> 00:16:39,280
You're a natural.

391
00:16:40,130 --> 00:16:41,080
Thank you.

392
00:16:41,650 --> 00:16:42,920
I think so, too.

393
00:16:45,490 --> 00:16:46,270
Blinker.

394
00:16:47,260 --> 00:16:49,800
All right, now make this left turn.

395
00:16:51,040 --> 00:16:52,610
Okay, don't circle this time.

396
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:55,210
Just keep going straight.

397
00:16:59,910 --> 00:17:00,860
‭What are you stopping for?

398
00:17:00,860 --> 00:17:03,270
You want me to go out on the street?

399
00:17:04,520 --> 00:17:06,710
It's where the car wants to go.

400
00:17:08,100 --> 00:17:09,030
Come on.

401
00:17:09,170 --> 00:17:10,910
What's the worst thing that could happen?

402
00:17:11,970 --> 00:17:15,560
I could run over someone and kill them.

403
00:17:16,810 --> 00:17:18,940
You have autism. You're not blind.

404
00:17:19,210 --> 00:17:20,780
And I'll be right here with you.

405
00:17:28,810 --> 00:17:31,030
Half Dome, here we come.

406
00:17:31,060 --> 00:17:31,980
Can I turn on the radio?

407
00:17:31,980 --> 00:17:33,910
- No! No, thank you. - Okay, okay.

408
00:17:46,660 --> 00:17:47,560
Nice.

409
00:17:52,630 --> 00:17:54,570
We believe moving up the separation surgery

410
00:17:54,570 --> 00:17:56,600
will lighten the load on Jenny's heart,

411
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,110
maybe allow it to recover a bit

412
00:17:58,110 --> 00:18:00,410
so a transplant won't even be necessary in the future.

413
00:18:00,410 --> 00:18:02,400
It is higher risk for Katie now,

414
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:05,100
given that her new kidney is still not fully functional.

415
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,700
What do you think we should do?

416
00:18:07,710 --> 00:18:09,900
It's your bodies. Your decision.

417
00:18:09,900 --> 00:18:12,150
- Mom, stop it. - No, I'm serious.

418
00:18:12,150 --> 00:18:16,340
I raised you both to be strong and independent, and you are.

419
00:18:16,990 --> 00:18:19,410
So whatever you decide, I'll support.

420
00:18:23,300 --> 00:18:24,270
Let's do it.

421
00:18:25,260 --> 00:18:27,230
Go ahead. Chop us in half.

422
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:29,470
Katie?

423
00:18:29,950 --> 00:18:31,570
We obviously need both your consent.

424
00:18:31,570 --> 00:18:33,790
- Okay. - You sure?

425
00:18:33,790 --> 00:18:36,120
You want to talk more? Have any questions?

426
00:18:36,530 --> 00:18:38,580
No. I'm good. Let's do it.

427
00:18:43,050 --> 00:18:44,700
I want a car.

428
00:18:44,850 --> 00:18:45,890
So get one.

429
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:47,270
You've been driving a half-hour,

430
00:18:47,270 --> 00:18:49,620
and you're already better than half the people in San Jose.

431
00:18:49,620 --> 00:18:51,850
I get distracted when I'm alone.

432
00:18:52,590 --> 00:18:54,540
That's why I miss my bus sometimes.

433
00:18:54,630 --> 00:18:58,160
Dr. Glassman thinks I'd do the same thing driving.

434
00:18:58,160 --> 00:18:59,920
He's probably right.

435
00:19:02,540 --> 00:19:03,740
Want to have some fun?

436
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:06,800
- I'm already having fun. - Stop the car.

437
00:19:06,950 --> 00:19:08,520
- Why? - Just do it.

438
00:19:11,290 --> 00:19:12,290
Thank you.

439
00:19:12,630 --> 00:19:15,570
Don't worry. We're the only car on the road right now.

440
00:19:16,650 --> 00:19:17,960
Put your left foot on the brake.

441
00:19:18,890 --> 00:19:19,660
Okay.

442
00:19:19,780 --> 00:19:20,820
There we go.

443
00:19:21,370 --> 00:19:24,160
Now hold it all the way down. There you go.

444
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:27,510
Okay, now floor the gas with your right foot.

445
00:19:29,970 --> 00:19:32,050
I-I don't know about this.

446
00:19:32,050 --> 00:19:33,250
No, it's okay. It's okay.

447
00:19:33,250 --> 00:19:36,890
Now slowly ease your left foot off the brake...

448
00:19:39,180 --> 00:19:41,010
until you hear...

449
00:19:41,650 --> 00:19:42,430
this.

450
00:19:42,430 --> 00:19:44,530
I smell smoke.

451
00:19:45,140 --> 00:19:46,610
Yeah, that's the point, Shaun.

452
00:19:46,610 --> 00:19:48,730
It's burning rubber. Do it again.

453
00:19:50,670 --> 00:19:51,460
Okay.

454
00:19:58,030 --> 00:19:59,720
Now, this is fun.

455
00:20:02,080 --> 00:20:03,130
Okay, that's enough.

456
00:20:03,130 --> 00:20:04,950
We need some rubber left to get us home.

457
00:20:05,930 --> 00:20:07,370
I am burning rubber.

458
00:20:07,370 --> 00:20:09,400
- Okay, Shaun, it's time to stop. ‭- Okay.

459
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:13,280
Shaun, take your other foot off the gas!

460
00:20:13,430 --> 00:20:14,430
Shaun, look out!

461
00:20:16,050 --> 00:20:18,650
It's the other foot! Other foot!

462
00:20:18,650 --> 00:20:19,860
It's the other foot! It's the other foot!

463
00:20:19,860 --> 00:20:20,840
It's the other foot!

464
00:20:24,190 --> 00:20:25,650
Dr. Ko and I have been working for months

465
00:20:25,650 --> 00:20:27,900
to map the structure of Jenny and Katie's brain.

466
00:20:28,120 --> 00:20:28,890
Don't you mean "Brains"?

467
00:20:28,890 --> 00:20:31,670
Actually, while different regions operate independently for each sister,

468
00:20:31,670 --> 00:20:33,130
there is a single brain mass.

469
00:20:33,130 --> 00:20:35,030
That's why all their previous neurosurgeons

470
00:20:35,030 --> 00:20:37,060
insisted separation was impossible.

471
00:20:37,060 --> 00:20:39,110
The real problem won't be dividing their brains

472
00:20:39,110 --> 00:20:41,250
but dividing their veins.

473
00:20:41,530 --> 00:20:44,900
They share a single sagittal sinus vein.

474
00:20:45,690 --> 00:20:46,690
Which we'll give to Jenny.

475
00:20:46,690 --> 00:20:50,140
Then we'll create a new one for Katie using a grafted vein from her leg.

476
00:20:50,140 --> 00:20:52,570
Nice. You've gotten them up to speed fast.

477
00:20:52,570 --> 00:20:54,800
Well, with 6 months of prep to do in 12 hours,

478
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:55,900
it was their only choice.

479
00:20:56,190 --> 00:20:57,650
So, let's get started.

480
00:20:57,720 --> 00:20:58,600
- I crashed. - We didn't.

481
00:20:58,600 --> 00:21:00,120
- Yes, I- I crashed. - We just...

482
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,460
- I hit something. - Shaun. Shaun.

483
00:21:01,460 --> 00:21:03,710
I hit something. I did. I hit something.

484
00:21:03,710 --> 00:21:04,570
- Shaun, you... - I know I did.

485
00:21:04,570 --> 00:21:05,960
- I felt it. I crashed. - Shaun, you didn't crash.

486
00:21:05,960 --> 00:21:06,890
- Yes. - You just drove off the road...

487
00:21:06,890 --> 00:21:08,210
- No. -And it was totally my fault.

488
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:10,280
No, you're wrong. Nuh- unh. I hit something.

489
00:21:10,280 --> 00:21:11,080
- No, you didn't. - I felt it.

490
00:21:11,080 --> 00:21:13,200
- I crashed. I crashed. - No, Shaun, look at me.

491
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:13,740
Calm down. Calm.

492
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:15,870
- Okay. Okay. - Look at me. Look at me.

493
00:21:16,070 --> 00:21:17,680
Breathe. Whatever happened,

494
00:21:17,680 --> 00:21:19,970
whatever you felt, you did nothing wrong.

495
00:21:20,010 --> 00:21:22,740
It was all my fault, okay?

496
00:21:25,590 --> 00:21:29,260
Okay. Dr. Glassman... He was right.

497
00:21:29,260 --> 00:21:32,880
I-I should not be allowed to drive.

498
00:21:33,130 --> 00:21:34,080
No, no.

499
00:21:39,260 --> 00:21:39,760
Shaun.

500
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:42,010
No, I'm not going to drive, thank you.

501
00:21:42,010 --> 00:21:44,790
Yeah, I...I know. No one is.

502
00:21:45,630 --> 00:21:47,890
'Cause you were right. We did hit something.

503
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:05,310
Everything is still looking good.

504
00:22:05,930 --> 00:22:07,480
If you need anything during the night,

505
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:08,930
just press your call button.

506
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:11,390
Is Jenny asleep?

507
00:22:11,470 --> 00:22:12,140
Yeah.

508
00:22:12,620 --> 00:22:14,170
Where's Dr. Andrews?

509
00:22:14,290 --> 00:22:17,680
He is with Dr. Ko and Dr. Melendez.

510
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:20,700
They're working to finalize the surgical protocol for tomorrow.

511
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:22,870
I need to talk to him.

512
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:24,900
Is there anything I can do?

513
00:22:27,710 --> 00:22:29,080
I changed my mind.

514
00:22:29,080 --> 00:22:31,950
I don't want to do the separation surgery.

515
00:22:34,720 --> 00:22:36,140
I'll go find him right away.

516
00:22:44,150 --> 00:22:46,500
I understand she's scared, but without this surgery,

517
00:22:46,500 --> 00:22:48,280
there is a good chance both of them die.

518
00:22:48,280 --> 00:22:49,300
Have you talked to the mother?

519
00:22:49,300 --> 00:22:52,040
She refuses to weigh in, insists it's their decision.

520
00:22:52,040 --> 00:22:53,530
Let me try and talk to her.

521
00:22:53,530 --> 00:22:54,890
I don't think that's a good idea.

522
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:57,860
You invented the technique you're gonna use to separate them.

523
00:22:58,660 --> 00:23:01,550
- So? - So she's not even close to objective.

524
00:23:01,550 --> 00:23:04,180
Okay, now is not the time to be worrying about lawsuits.

525
00:23:04,180 --> 00:23:05,030
That's my job.

526
00:23:05,030 --> 00:23:06,920
And our job is saving these girls' lives.

527
00:23:06,920 --> 00:23:09,570
Okay, take it easy. We're all on the same team here.

528
00:23:11,930 --> 00:23:13,670
- I'll talk to her. - You've already talked to her.

529
00:23:13,670 --> 00:23:15,020
I will try again.

530
00:23:18,160 --> 00:23:19,330
Browne should do it.

531
00:23:20,740 --> 00:23:21,460
Me?

532
00:23:22,410 --> 00:23:24,710
We need someone that an 18-year-old girl trusts.

533
00:23:25,820 --> 00:23:27,880
She's also the best communicator out of all of us.

534
00:23:33,430 --> 00:23:34,310
Okay.

535
00:23:35,880 --> 00:23:37,110
We'll give Katie the night to think it over.

536
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:38,670
Browne, you'll talk to her in the morning.

537
00:23:38,680 --> 00:23:40,330
Get her to consent to this surgery.

538
00:23:40,610 --> 00:23:42,950
And if I'm not able to do that?

539
00:23:46,710 --> 00:23:49,330
It's not a big deal. Cars break.

540
00:23:49,330 --> 00:23:52,450
That's why God makes mechanics... and booze.

541
00:23:52,700 --> 00:23:53,890
Two shots of tequila, please.

542
00:23:53,890 --> 00:23:56,210
I'm not thirsty.

543
00:23:56,210 --> 00:23:58,690
You don't drink tequila because you're thirsty.

544
00:24:00,420 --> 00:24:02,030
Have you ever been drunk?

545
00:24:03,920 --> 00:24:05,010
Never?

546
00:24:05,050 --> 00:24:09,220
Eight years of college a-and not one frat party?

547
00:24:09,330 --> 00:24:12,020
Tailgating? Your roommate's 21st birthday?

548
00:24:12,020 --> 00:24:13,360
What is your job?

549
00:24:13,580 --> 00:24:15,200
Now you're interested in my job?

550
00:24:16,190 --> 00:24:16,910
Yes.

551
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:19,280
I'm an automotive engineer.

552
00:24:19,280 --> 00:24:24,050
I work for a start-up that's developing new designs for self-driving cars.

553
00:24:24,050 --> 00:24:25,360
Do you like it?

554
00:24:26,550 --> 00:24:27,390
No.

555
00:24:29,570 --> 00:24:31,000
I like to build things,

556
00:24:31,030 --> 00:24:34,820
